def enableMumbai(): Unit = {

   spark.sparkContext.hadoopConfiguration.set("fs.s3a.impl", "org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.S3AFileSystem")

   spark.sparkContext.hadoopConfiguration.set("fs.s3a.endpoint", "s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com")
}

enableMumbai()

val settings = new Settings

paragraphs.title: Features Spark job template
paragraphs.text:
object Features {
    
import com.paytm.map.features.config.BaseDFSConfig
import com.paytm.map.features.utils.Settings
import com.paytm.map.features.SparkJobBootstrap
import com.paytm.map.features.SparkJob
import com.paytm.map.features.SparkJobValidation
import com.paytm.map.features.SparkJobValidations.DailyJobValidation
import com.paytm.map.features.utils.ArgsUtils
import org.joda.time.DateTime

import org.apache.spark.sql._

object Template extends TemplateJob with SparkJob with SparkJobBootstrap

trait TemplateJob {
    this: SparkJob =>
    
    val JobName = "Template"
    
    def validate(spark: SparkSession, settings: Settings, args: Array[String]): SparkJobValidation = {
        DailyJobValidation.validate(spark, args)
    }
    
     def runJob(spark: SparkSession, settings: Settings, args: Array[String]): Unit = {
        
        val targetDate: DateTime = ArgsUtils.getTargetDate(args)
        val targetDateStr = targetDate.toString(ArgsUtils.formatter)
        val lookBackDays: Int = args(1).toInt
        val startDateStr = targetDate.minusDays(lookBackDays).toString(ArgsUtils.formatter)
        
        // INPUT
        val input =  readTableV3(spark, getLatestSnapshotV3ByName(s"marketplace.sales_order_item", settings.datalakeDfs.daaSQueryEndPoint), targetDateStr, startDateStr)
        // OUTPUT
        val output = "s3a://midgar-aws-workspace/home/wyu/stg/temp/dummy"
        
        // Register table
        val sales = spark.read.parquet(input)
        sales.createOrReplaceTempView("sales")
        sales.printSchema
        
        // Feature sql query, output dataset should have the columns: `customer_id: LongType, dt: DateType, feature1, feature2, ...`
        val df = spark.sql(
        """
          |select
          | customer_id,
          | dt,
          | sum(selling_price) as total_txn_size
          |from sales
          |group by customer_id, dt
        """.stripMargin)
        
        // Show output
        // df.show

        // Write output
        spark.conf.set("spark.sql.sources.partitionOverwriteMode", "DYNAMIC")
        df
        .write
        .mode("overwrite")
        .partitionBy("dt")
        .parquet(output)
     }
}

}
